<h2 id="privacy">Privacy + storage</h2>

<p>convertFlow runs entirely in your browser. Specifically:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Files you open, paste, or upload stay in browser memory and localStorage. They are never uploaded to a server.</li>
  <li>The only network requests are: (a) Hugging Face when you explicitly click <strong>↑ HF Hub</strong> using your own token, and (b) optional anonymous Plausible analytics for product usage stats — disable via Settings → Privacy.</li>
  <li>localStorage keys all begin with <code>dataprep</code>. The Settings → "Clear all stored data" button removes every one of them.</li>
  <li>Files larger than 3MB are kept in session memory only — they do not survive a reload.</li>
  <li>If storage fills up, the oldest files are evicted automatically (with a warning).</li>
</ul>

